OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 23 Jul to Sat 1 AugFFor
OL,6,Fmuch of the UK, dry at first with
OL,7,Fsunny spells. Northern and
OL,8,Fnorthwestern areas will be cloudier
OL,9,Fwith occasional patchy rain or
OL,10,Fdrizzle. Towards the weekend and
OL,11,Fperhaps into the start of next week,
OL,12,Fperhaps a more unsettled period with
OL,13,Frain at times, especially across
OL,14,Fnorthern parts of the UK. This rain
OL,15,Fmay very well reach southern areas
OL,16,Ftoo, but could be light and patchy
OL,17,Fhere. Confidence becomes lower as we
OL,18,Fhead into next week, but there are
OL,19,Fsigns that high pressure will return,
OL,20,Fwhich means dry conditions would
OL,21,Fresume, especially in the south. Winds
OL,22,Fwill be mostly light or moderate,
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Foccasionally fresh around northern
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fcoasts. Temperatures are expected to
OL,25,Fbe near or above normal, warmest in
OL,26,Fthe south, perhaps becoming very warm
